By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Vice President Yemi Osinbajo has expressed sadness over the sudden demise of Mr. Ojima Omale (aka OJBEST). The VP condolences was contained in a statement released via twitter handle by his spokesperson, Laolu Akande on Monday. Osinbanjo who described OJBEST as a talented, creative & dedicated to his craft, prayed God to comfort his family. According to the statement, “The VP is “deeply saddened by news of the sudden death of Mr. Ojima Omale, aka OJBEST, 28, my young enterprising shoemaker and friend… He was talented, creative & dedicated to his craft.” He prays God will comfort his family & that his memory remains blessed. Olalekan Adetayo Abuja  -  The Acting President, Yemi Osinbajo, on Tuesday, said he received the news of the death of Channels TV State House Correspondent, Mr. Chukwuma Onuekwusi, with great sadness. In a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mr. Laolu Akande, the Acting President extended… In "News" •The late Mr. Simeon Nwakaudu PORT HARCOURT (SundiataPost) - Mr. Simeon Nwakaudu, media assistant to Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, is dead. Nwakaudu died on Sunday afternoon after a brief illness. He passed on at the Rivers State University Teaching Hospital (RSUTH) where he was being treated for an undisclosed… In "News" By Kingsley Okoye Abuja - President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has expressed shock and sadness over the tragic news of the death of Sen. Ben Uwajumogu (APC-Imo). Lawan in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr Ola Awoniyi commiserated with the family of the deceased senator… In "News"